thread.title_full: Australian market set to open lower

author: news.com.au
title: lower
text:
Tuesday finished higher.
 lower after Wall Street tumbled on worries about global growth and the burgeoning Volkswagen emissions scandal.
At 0645 AEST on Wednesday, the share price index futures contract was down 70 points at 5,086.
No major economic news is expected on Wednesday.
In equities news, Nufarm is expected to post full year results while BHP Billiton releases its annual report.
Meanwhile, the Tax Summit continues.
 Tuesday finished higher despite losing much of its early morning gains as investors nervously await key Chinese economic data.
